<m0>NAMES IN THE NEWS<ql>
<m1><ue5><m0>Broward parks name new superintendent<ql>
<m1><ue5><styl>names<ql>
<styl>indentl,10p9,6p8<ql>
<ep>
<m0>  <m0>Robert E. Wright <m0>has been appointed superintendent of planning and engineering for the Broward County Division of Parks and Recreation. He is responsible for planning and design at the division's system of 73 regional parks, unincorporated area neighborhood parks and environmentally sensitive lands.<ep>
   <m0>Sonia ``Sonny'' Ginsberg, <m0>president of Achievement and Rehabilitation Centers in Sunrise, has retired after 20 years. Ginsberg, who joined ARC's Broward staff in 1977, was the driving force behind the construction of the agency's facility, which opened in 1991. Her replacement at the agency, which helps the developmentally disabled and their families, is <m0>Robert A. Burton, <m0>former chief operating officer of Mount Sinai Medical Center in Miami Beach.<ep>
   Fort Lauderdale's <m0>Hans J. Hvide<m0> and <m0>Frederick G. Ruffner Jr. <m0>and Hillsboro Beach's <m0>Kay Smith <m0>have been named to the 1996 Nova Southeastern University Entrepreneur Hall of Fame. Hvide has led companies for 60 years that manage, construct and broker ships. Ruffner has built a niche in reference book publishing. Smith is a motivational speaker.<ql>
